<seg id=1> Fujian to Strongly Promote Fujian-Taiwan Economic and Trade Cooperation this Year </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua Press Agency, Fuzhou, January 10, Telegram (Reporter Xu Ting):  Fujian Province recently stated that it would strongly promote Fujian-Taiwan economic and trade cooperation this year, take more bids from Taiwanese businessmen, strengthen relations with large Taiwanese enterprises and financial groups, court some large Taiwanese investment projects to come to Fujian and invest, strongly develop trade with Taiwan and develop cooperation with Taiwan regarding fishing, production, and labor matters. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The competent department of Fujian Province recently established new trade measures to accelerate development of foreign business and trade, intensifying the reformation of foreign business and trade enterprises, maintaining stable export growth, continuing expansion in the use of foreign capital, and so forth as the main contents of the foreign business and trade work of this province in 1998. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Fujian is one of the coastal regions of China with the fastest development of foreign business and trade. </seg>
<seg id=5> Gross foreign trade import-exports for this province reached US$20 billion last year, actually employed foreign capital exceeded US$4.1 billion, and the total amount of foreign contract engineering and labor cooperation reached US$355 million. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> It is reported that the main content of these new measures is to develop economy of management; promote the strategic reorganization of province-owned companies engaged in foreign trade, with a focus on assembly enterprise groups; increase the export of support industry products; and successfully conduct the Foreign Investment Invitation Conference and 1998 China Investment and Trade Discussion Conference held in Hong Kong. </seg>
</p>
